{
  "stem": "14168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said-- he said, I do not feel guilty for what my parents did, but it is so abhorrent to me that I can assure you we will-- we know we young Germans have a responsibility for the future.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And very slowly, bridges were built, and I talked to these people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I found that they were-- most of them, at least, wanted to start over a new leaf, a new book, as far as Germany was concerned.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had some very open dialogues with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And yes, I became legal counsel to the German Consulate General, then later on to the French Consulate General, to the Austrian Consulate General.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In fact, the one who made me, appointed me as the Austrian-- as a legal counsel to the Austrian Consulate General is the current president of Austria, Thomas Klestil, with whom I have had a friendship ever since, and who has invited me to come to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Also with the Italians, the Italian Consulate General.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I have decorations from all of these governments for service to them, loyal service to them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In addition to that, I-- I represent most European governments here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that's my current status.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Unfortunately, coming back to my personal life, my lovely wife Ursula passed away in November 1989, after two years' battle against cancer.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Two years, I was on my own.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I was by myself.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then I-- I learned that it would be very hard for me to live alone, and I had the good fortune of meeting Birgitta, my current wife, my present wife, who has given me a lovely new home, and to whom I got married over two years ago.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
